By Anayo Onukwugha, Port Harcourt Operatives of the Rivers State Police Command, in a joint operation with a local vigilante outfit, today arrested a notorious kidnapper and leader of Greenlanders Cult Group, Honest Digbara popularly known as Boboski. Boboski, who had been terrorizing communities in Ogoni ethnic nationality of Rivers State, was arrested at about 2:30am, at Koro Community in Tai local government area of the state. The notorious kidnapper was arrested along with his second-in-command, who is also his immediate younger brother Rivers State Governor, Nyesom Ezenwo Wike, had earlier this year placed a N30million bounty on the wanted kidnapper.